THE body of a 38-year-old man who was reported missing on Sunday, 26 December in the Free State has been discovered by residents at Matlwangtlwang kasi in Steynsrus. Brigadier Motantsi Makhele said the dead man’s family opened a missing person’s case on Wednesday, 29 December, after failing to contact or locate him. “While the matter was reported, a body of a drowned person was reported. Upon arrival at the scene, the deceased, who was retrieved by police divers, matched the description of the missing person,” Makhele said. He said an inquest docket was opened and that they were not suspecting foul play so far. “Post mortem results later revealed that the person had drowned in the river,” Makhele added. Free State provincial commissioner, Lieutenant-General Baile Motswenyane, has appealed to residents to be careful near streams and dams. “We’re aware that we are experiencing high rainfall throughout the festive season. I’m humbly pleading with the community to stay away from dams and rivers as they can become easily swept away by the water which can lead to drowning,” Motswenyane said.